Warzymice  (German Reinkendorf) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kołbaskowo, within Police County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland, close to the German border. It lies approximately  south-west of Police and borders with the regional capital Szczecin ( away from city-centre).
